WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:02.247
[guitar music plays]

00:03.480 --> 00:04.527
[sizzling]

00:08.640 --> 00:10.483
[water running]

00:14.560 --> 00:16.562
[Dion] What do you mean
the restaurant's not happening?

00:19.400 --> 00:20.890
What are you doing?
What the hell?

00:21.040 --> 00:22.405
I had a fight with my dad.

00:22.640 --> 00:24.847
- He hit T.J.
- What?!

00:24.960 --> 00:26.371
I found bruises on him,

00:26.440 --> 00:27.851
so I went to my dad's house, and I--

00:27.920 --> 00:30.082
[Dion] Oh, dude, no, no.
You got it all wrong.

00:30.160 --> 00:32.891
Look, I saw T.J.'s bruises yesterday

00:32.960 --> 00:34.450
before he went to your dad's.

00:35.240 --> 00:37.004
T.J.'s getting bullied at school.

00:37.080 --> 00:38.127
What?

00:38.800 --> 00:41.565
In hindsight,
I probably should have mentioned it.

00:41.640 --> 00:43.847
- Probably?
- Look, I knew you'd overreact.

00:43.920 --> 00:45.729
I didn't overreact. I reacted.

00:45.800 --> 00:47.962
Hey, you had a throw-down
with our investor,

00:48.040 --> 00:49.565
- who's in a wheelchair.
- Yeah, well,

00:49.640 --> 00:50.926
if you'd told me about the bruises,

00:51.040 --> 00:52.041
it never would have happened.

00:52.120 --> 00:54.009
You're right. All right. I'm-- I'm sorry.

00:54.080 --> 00:56.686
So, T.J.'s getting bullied?

00:57.040 --> 00:59.327
Who is it? I got to report this.

00:59.400 --> 01:00.526
Dude, dude, dude, please, come on.

01:00.600 --> 01:02.125
Just-- just slow your roll, huh?

01:02.760 --> 01:05.161
T.J. made it clear he wants
to handle this himself.

01:06.080 --> 01:08.128
Wait a minute, what, my s--
my son's talking to you now?

01:08.200 --> 01:09.486
Y-- you'll only make it worse.

01:09.560 --> 01:11.528
Yeah?
Well, I'm the father, okay?

01:11.600 --> 01:12.647
I got to do something.

01:12.760 --> 01:15.570
T., Just think back to when
you were getting your ass kicked.

01:15.960 --> 01:17.689
All right?
Look, if your dad had come to school

01:17.760 --> 01:18.761
saying his son was getting bullied,

01:18.840 --> 01:20.365
what do you think
would have happened?

01:20.440 --> 01:21.885
Huh-- What,
your beat-downs would have been

01:21.960 --> 01:23.007
exponentially worse.

01:23.240 --> 01:25.288
Yeah? Well, lucky for me,
my dad couldn't care less.

01:25.360 --> 01:28.204
Look, you're not remembering
what it was like to be a kid.

01:29.560 --> 01:33.087
I remember exactly what it was like, okay?
It was hell.

01:33.320 --> 01:37.245
Until some little crazy-ass punk
pulled a knife on those guys

01:37.320 --> 01:38.446
and got them to leave me alone.

01:39.280 --> 01:41.647
Look, T.J. doesn't have
a friend like you.

01:45.120 --> 01:47.521
Look, you are gonna apologize
to Aidan, though, right?

01:47.600 --> 01:48.681
I'm not doing anything,

01:48.760 --> 01:51.366
until I deal with
what's going on with my son.

01:54.920 --> 01:56.445
I can assure you that there's

01:56.520 --> 01:58.363
a zero-tolerance policy for bullying.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.287
- [counselor] Did anyone see it happen?
- I don't know.

02:01.360 --> 02:03.931
Did T.J. indicate who hit him?

02:04.000 --> 02:05.650
- No.
- Then how do you know

02:05.720 --> 02:07.484
he got the bruises at school?

02:08.120 --> 02:09.723
He could have fallen at the park...

02:09.919 --> 02:11.649
- [scoffs]
- [counselor] or at home.

02:12.600 --> 02:15.604
I know what bruises look like
on a kid who's getting beat up.

02:15.720 --> 02:17.131
Were you bullied?

02:18.120 --> 02:19.087
[counselor] Or did...

02:19.200 --> 02:21.521
did something happen
at home growing up?

02:21.720 --> 02:22.960
How is that relevant?

02:23.800 --> 02:25.211
How did you get this?

02:25.720 --> 02:27.210
I fell at the park.

02:35.320 --> 02:37.163
What? What is that?

02:37.320 --> 02:39.766
Well, statistics show
that violence in the home

02:39.840 --> 02:41.080
is learned behavior.

02:41.360 --> 02:42.407
[scoffs]

02:42.680 --> 02:44.444
First you threaten to take my kid away.

02:44.560 --> 02:46.688
Now-- now you accuse me
of beating him?

02:46.760 --> 02:48.489
I'm not accusing you of anything.

02:48.560 --> 02:50.881
- Just relax.
- Don't tell me to relax!

02:51.520 --> 02:53.761
Okay, my son is getting...

02:59.480 --> 03:01.050
[sighs]

03:02.080 --> 03:03.923
I don't keep a violent home.

03:05.080 --> 03:07.321
He's getting bullied here, okay?

03:07.400 --> 03:09.801
And, I can't seem to protect him.

03:09.880 --> 03:12.121
Without proof,
I can't very well question

03:12.200 --> 03:13.531
every kid in the school.

03:13.680 --> 03:16.160
Okay, so wh-- what can you do?

03:16.240 --> 03:17.651
I can look into it.

03:18.840 --> 03:22.731
It's my priority that T.J. at least feels
safe while he's at school.

03:24.200 --> 03:25.406
In the meantime,

03:25.480 --> 03:28.324
I suggest you lean on
T.J.'s support person.

03:28.920 --> 03:30.763
Dion seems very committed.

03:31.960 --> 03:33.564
[counselor] I'm glad you got some help.

03:35.120 --> 03:36.963
Yeah, Jimmy, that's it.

03:37.040 --> 03:39.202
Yeah, remember demo's on Wednesday,
okay?

03:39.320 --> 03:41.368
Listen, man, I-- I'll call you back.

03:41.960 --> 03:44.201
Huh? You feel good?
Huh? You feel like a good daddy?

03:44.280 --> 03:46.248
You tell me, Dr. Patras.

03:46.640 --> 03:48.165
- What?
- Support person?

03:48.240 --> 03:49.366
[chuckling]
Oh, that?

03:49.440 --> 03:50.851
Yeah, yeah,
that was for you, bro.

03:50.920 --> 03:52.445
You know,
to get the shrink off your back.

03:52.520 --> 03:54.010
So you lied to her.

03:54.080 --> 03:56.765
Yeah. Fine. I apologize.

03:56.880 --> 03:58.370
Look, see how easy that is?

03:58.440 --> 04:00.488
Come on, let's go to Aidan's
and do the same thing.

04:00.560 --> 04:01.607
No way.

04:01.720 --> 04:03.609
You have to.
I already hired a contractor.

04:03.720 --> 04:04.767
With what money?

04:04.840 --> 04:07.127
With the money we're gonna get
when you apologize to your dad.

04:07.240 --> 04:09.811
- The man stuck a gun in my face.
- All right, fine.

04:09.880 --> 04:10.927
I understand.

04:11.240 --> 04:12.890
Hey, you know what?
Let's see who's next

04:12.960 --> 04:15.327
in our magical book of investors,
shall we?

04:15.440 --> 04:16.726
Come on.
Let's take a look.

04:16.920 --> 04:18.728
Uh, no. No.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.290
And no.

04:26.280 --> 04:28.567
You got to walk me through this
one more time.

04:30.400 --> 04:34.086
The guy's in a wheelchair,
and you're standing.

04:34.920 --> 04:37.048
He's 70. You're, what, like have his age?

04:37.120 --> 04:38.645
- He still manages to kick--
- Okay, would-- would you stop?

04:38.720 --> 04:40.722
Look, I'm just trying to figure out
the logistics here, all right?

04:40.840 --> 04:43.002
- All right, just-- just stop.
- All right, all right, all right.

04:43.080 --> 04:44.445
Look, but seriously,

04:44.800 --> 04:48.168
if he tries to roll up on you again,
I got your back, man.

04:48.280 --> 04:50.282
Come on. Quick and painless, bro.

04:53.200 --> 04:56.204
Whatever it is, make it fast.
I got real business.

04:58.800 --> 04:59.847
[Aidan] So...?

05:01.840 --> 05:04.571
So, last night, I may have overreacted.

05:04.640 --> 05:06.483
You know what? He totally overreacted.

05:06.560 --> 05:09.723
T.J. got his bruises from a bully
at school,

05:10.360 --> 05:12.124
[Tommy] a fact I was unaware of

05:12.200 --> 05:15.761
because somebody chose not to tell me.

05:17.120 --> 05:19.088
Why are you here?

05:22.160 --> 05:23.685
To apologize...

05:24.120 --> 05:29.001
and, despite recent misunderstandings,

05:29.520 --> 05:32.683
ask if you'll reconsider
investing in our restaurant.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.206
I never said I wouldn't.

05:34.680 --> 05:36.603
We fought. You lost.

05:36.720 --> 05:40.042
And we have a contract,
which you read, right?

05:40.120 --> 05:41.167
- Yes.
- Course.

05:41.720 --> 05:44.371
Well, get to work.
You're opening in four weeks.

05:44.840 --> 05:46.365
- Four weeks?
- Yeah.

05:47.280 --> 05:48.725
I've invited some developers

05:48.800 --> 05:50.882
who are building
eight square blocks of condos.

05:51.360 --> 05:53.249
What better place
to pitch them my business

05:53.360 --> 05:54.850
than at my new restaurant?

05:55.480 --> 05:57.403
And none of that pussy fish crap.

05:57.520 --> 05:59.170
[Aidan] These guys are carnivores.

05:59.280 --> 06:01.601
So there better be blood
coming out of something,

06:02.080 --> 06:03.923
besides your vagina.

06:07.280 --> 06:09.965
- Got a problem?
- [Tommy] Are you out of your mind?

06:10.040 --> 06:13.567
- Four weeks? That's-- that's not--
- It's not a problem.

06:14.160 --> 06:17.403
No, no, no, it's-- We're good.

06:20.440 --> 06:22.522
I want to hear the other guy say it.

06:22.720 --> 06:24.927
Yeah, we're good.

06:27.120 --> 06:29.600
All right, you're good.
I'm good. Everybody's good.

06:29.680 --> 06:31.409
When I accused you of hitting my son,

06:31.600 --> 06:32.931
why didn't you say anything?

06:33.160 --> 06:35.128
I wanted to see what you'd do.

06:37.400 --> 06:40.847
[mid-tempo music plays]

06:43.880 --> 06:46.565
That 75 grand is for start-up costs.

06:47.440 --> 06:49.761
Weekly installments to follow.

06:51.520 --> 06:53.204
Thank you, Mr. Moran.

06:57.680 --> 06:59.409
Quick and painless, bro.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.007
[laughs]

07:03.040 --> 07:06.089
Man, with this,
I can get my Groen braising pan,

07:06.160 --> 07:09.084
my Tri-Star 48-inch Radiant Charbroiler.

07:09.160 --> 07:11.891
No, you know what? Make that two.

07:12.280 --> 07:14.123
Eyes on the prize, baby.

07:16.240 --> 07:18.607
[mid-tempo music plays]

07:22.480 --> 07:26.007
♪ Fever dreams ♪

07:26.080 --> 07:28.447
♪ Or so it seems ♪

07:30.840 --> 07:32.365
♪ All I see is ♪

07:32.480 --> 07:34.847
♪ What used to be ♪

07:34.920 --> 07:37.048
♪ Fever dreams ♪

07:37.760 --> 07:40.923
♪ I've been around
I'm lost and found ♪

07:41.560 --> 07:44.882
♪ I burned it all
to the ground ♪

07:44.960 --> 07:48.681
♪ Ashes to ashes
hope that dashes ♪

07:48.880 --> 07:51.326
♪ My own mystery ♪

07:52.400 --> 07:57.201
♪ And all I see
is what used to be ♪

08:02.080 --> 08:04.481
[guitar music plays]

08:09.280 --> 08:10.850
[Tommy]
I've never talked about my father here.

08:11.080 --> 08:12.969
You know, I don't want to waste my breath.

08:13.040 --> 08:14.804
Suddenly, he's back in my life,

08:14.880 --> 08:17.645
and I... I don't know how to deal with it.

08:18.840 --> 08:21.161
He's, uh--
He's the main investor in our restaurant,

08:21.240 --> 08:23.971
which means the bastard's
actually my business partner.

08:24.320 --> 08:26.004
And it's all happening way too fast.

08:26.600 --> 08:29.206
And we don't know a damn thing
about running a restaurant.

08:29.320 --> 08:32.164
That part was all-- all Rie's thing.

08:35.240 --> 08:37.447
I'm just screwed.

08:40.600 --> 08:42.044
Let me lend a hand.

08:42.360 --> 08:46.922
I could manage your restaurant for you,
just like at my sister's.

08:47.560 --> 08:50.530
Oh, that's-- that's very sweet, really.

08:50.600 --> 08:53.365
But, uh, I mean,
I-- I can't afford to hire a manager.

08:53.440 --> 08:54.521
[sighs]

08:54.920 --> 08:57.810
- Pay me when you can.
- Really? I mean...

08:58.840 --> 09:00.968
could you even handle two restaurants?

09:01.080 --> 09:02.127
I can try.

09:02.200 --> 09:05.488
I mean, yeah... Thanks.

09:05.600 --> 09:07.762
Just let me know when to start.

09:07.840 --> 09:09.285
How about yesterday?

09:09.400 --> 09:10.447
[both chuckle]

09:16.680 --> 09:19.889
Did you put down that <i>dupek</i> chef
like I told you to?

09:20.200 --> 09:23.044
<i>That dupek chef will be
paying us every week, so no.</i>

09:23.120 --> 09:25.361
Bullshit.
Where's he getting it?

09:25.480 --> 09:27.084
From an investor.

09:27.200 --> 09:30.647
Patras is opening a new restaurant.
So we can collect on his debt

09:30.720 --> 09:33.690
<i>and have a place to legitimize our income.</i>

09:33.800 --> 09:36.167
<i>And what about that Giordano fig?</i>

09:36.240 --> 09:38.971
Don't worry, Pop.
I backed him way off.

09:39.160 --> 09:41.242
Back him off a bridge.

09:43.600 --> 09:46.046
You know why people
don't respect me anymore?

09:46.640 --> 09:48.961
<i>- Because you are soft.
- I'm not soft.</i>

09:49.040 --> 09:52.089
- [chuckles]
- I already took care of Chu's shipment.

09:52.960 --> 09:53.961
What do you mean?

09:54.040 --> 09:58.045
The Asians' merch
is now part of our inventory.

09:58.120 --> 10:03.809
<i>I said keep Chu out of our territory,
period.</i>

10:03.880 --> 10:06.690
Do you even think before you do things?

10:09.120 --> 10:10.531
<i>When you mentioned it, I assumed--</i>

10:10.600 --> 10:13.444
<i>I never said steal it!
[shouts] ldiota!</i>

10:16.160 --> 10:20.165
Now every gook east of Hong Kong
will be looking for this stuff.

10:22.800 --> 10:23.961
<i>Divide it up.</i>

10:25.240 --> 10:28.528
Hide it in five different places.

10:30.440 --> 10:32.841
<i>Don't touch it for a year.</i>

10:37.560 --> 10:39.562
[Jimmy] Months?! I don't know.

10:40.080 --> 10:41.650
Whatever it takes, Jimmy.

10:42.640 --> 10:44.927
Okay, wow.
All right, my guys will get it done,

10:45.040 --> 10:48.328
- especially if you're cooking for them.
- Ha, they'll eat like kings!

10:48.560 --> 10:51.006
- [Pilar] Hi. Hello.
- I got you set up in here.

10:51.880 --> 10:53.325
- [man] Hey.
- Hi. Pilar.

10:53.680 --> 10:55.569
You're so great about wanting to jump in,

10:55.680 --> 11:00.368
but, uh, with the time I had, this was
the best I could do, so-- Oh! Man!

11:01.760 --> 11:03.524
Ugh. Come in. Sorry.

11:04.600 --> 11:06.682
So, yeah, pretty standard stuff.

11:06.760 --> 11:09.570
Insurance forms, I-9s, balance sheets.

11:10.200 --> 11:13.170
Application for the liquor license.
That's important.

11:13.440 --> 11:15.807
We've got about $1,240 on account,

11:15.880 --> 11:19.043
and we just cashed
our start-up check for $75,000.

11:19.120 --> 11:21.361
- And, uh, where's that?
- Dion has it.

11:21.440 --> 11:24.762
[Dion] God, yes! I want to have
rough sex with these pans! Whoo!

11:25.080 --> 11:27.924
Hey! Give the receipts to Pilar!

11:28.800 --> 11:30.404
Yes. Receipts.

11:31.440 --> 11:32.487
[chuckles]

11:33.160 --> 11:34.207
So...

11:36.880 --> 11:39.565
I'm re-- I'm-- I'm glad you're here.

11:42.080 --> 11:44.765
- I really should, uh, dive in.
- Yeah. Yes, please.

11:44.840 --> 11:47.969
Um, can I get you anything?
Do you want tea or anything?

11:48.200 --> 11:50.168
Um, no. Thank you.

11:50.240 --> 11:51.571
Okay.

11:53.440 --> 11:56.728
Oh, urn, door closed, please.

11:58.520 --> 11:59.965
Thanks again.

12:07.720 --> 12:08.846
[cellphone vibrating]

12:09.480 --> 12:11.801
<i>Hola, cariño.
- [Pilar] Hey, Blanca.</i>

12:11.880 --> 12:13.211
¿Qué pasa?
You sound funny.

12:13.440 --> 12:15.044
No, I have good news.

12:15.200 --> 12:16.440
Did that wine guy ask you out?

12:16.520 --> 12:19.000
No, but I'm managing his restaurant.

12:19.720 --> 12:21.768
You know nothing about
managing a restaurant.

12:21.840 --> 12:23.410
I know a few things.

12:24.840 --> 12:26.251
I was just wondering...

12:26.800 --> 12:30.122
what does an H...VAC mean?

12:30.200 --> 12:32.248
<i>¡Ay, Dios mío!</i>

12:32.320 --> 12:34.322
Focus on the basics.
Keep track of the money.

12:34.760 --> 12:35.921
And the windows are stationary?

12:36.000 --> 12:37.809
No. Rie's idea was that these were

12:37.880 --> 12:40.201
sliding casement windows
so that--

12:40.320 --> 12:42.163
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
This is a mistake.

12:42.640 --> 12:44.130
- [Dion] Nope.
- [Tommy] What?

12:44.760 --> 12:46.842
What do we need two walk-ins for?

12:46.920 --> 12:48.160
One is for perishables.

12:48.240 --> 12:50.322
The other one is for curing
and aging our own meat.

12:50.400 --> 12:52.482
That is completely impractical.

12:52.560 --> 12:56.451
Dude, dude, our place is called Thirio,
right, meaning "beast."

12:56.520 --> 12:59.683
Now, if it's called Scallop,
sure, fine, whatever, but it's not.

12:59.840 --> 13:02.081
Besides,
me and Rie already talked this through.

13:02.160 --> 13:04.242
Oh, you and Rie already
talked this through? Where was I?

13:04.320 --> 13:05.367
T., T.,

13:05.560 --> 13:06.721
you are
the most brilliant somm

13:06.800 --> 13:08.211
in the whole
of the five boroughs.

13:08.280 --> 13:09.770
I wouldn't even begin
to tell you what to do

13:09.840 --> 13:12.923
with your wine list.
Just-- just relax, all right?

13:13.000 --> 13:14.604
Look, I got this.

13:17.440 --> 13:19.522
All right, who am I paying around here?
You?

13:21.640 --> 13:22.880
It's all there, man.

13:26.000 --> 13:28.367
[Anna] I get that you're having
a hard time,

13:29.680 --> 13:33.162
but I want you to know
that you're not alone.

13:33.240 --> 13:35.402
Other kids are having
a hard time, too.

13:35.480 --> 13:38.802
Not like you, but they're struggling.

13:38.960 --> 13:40.849
Like, there's the two Liams.

13:41.440 --> 13:46.082
Liam B. with his asthma.
Liam K. has those tantrums.

13:48.840 --> 13:52.561
Andre Walker has a very hard
time controlling his anger.

13:55.160 --> 13:58.642
[guitar music plays]

14:02.560 --> 14:03.846
[construction sounds]

14:03.920 --> 14:05.445
Oh, Tommy?

14:06.120 --> 14:07.201
You know Mose?

14:07.320 --> 14:08.970
- Yeah. Hey.
- Hey.

14:09.280 --> 14:11.408
- We should hire Mose.
- To do...?

14:11.480 --> 14:13.687
- Anything.
- Well, if I can't afford to pay you,

14:13.760 --> 14:15.091
I can't afford to pay him.

14:15.160 --> 14:16.571
We need all the help we can get,

14:16.640 --> 14:19.689
and Mose qualifies for some kind
of privately funded grant.

14:19.760 --> 14:22.730
Veterans with Disabilities
Reintegration Program.

14:22.880 --> 14:25.406
- Meaning...?
- We get paid to have Mose work here.

14:25.600 --> 14:27.204
Welcome to Thirio.

14:29.720 --> 14:31.882
It feels good to be a part of something.

14:32.440 --> 14:34.488
- What is that?
- Oven hood.

14:34.920 --> 14:38.481
- Impressive.
- Yeah, it should be for $9,250.

14:38.720 --> 14:40.848
Hey, is Dion giving you
the receipts?

14:40.920 --> 14:43.207
- I think so.
- Oh! Hey.

14:43.280 --> 14:46.045
Dang! I thought we
were getting the big one!

14:46.520 --> 14:49.091
- Hey, I'm kidding, man. I'm kidding.
- Look, hey, I think-- I think Pilar

14:49.200 --> 14:51.601
should be handling the money, all right?
She is our manager.

14:51.720 --> 14:54.883
- Yeah, it wasn't my idea.
- Hey, she's working for free, man.

14:55.080 --> 14:57.048
See? I told you she digs you.

14:57.120 --> 14:58.451
No, the point is that--

14:58.520 --> 15:00.329
No, the point is that I run the kitchen.

15:00.760 --> 15:01.921
I know what we need.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.684
Look, I have to go through her? No.

15:03.920 --> 15:05.968
- Come on, what's your concern here?
- Well, first of all--

15:06.040 --> 15:08.486
No, no! [laughing] No!

15:09.160 --> 15:11.367
Are you kidding me?!
