33:47.120 --> 33:49.248
<i>[Tommy] Wait, wait, wait,
wait, what's-- what's Stavros carrying?</i>

33:49.720 --> 33:52.007
- No, that's crap.
- You don't like what I'm stealing,

33:52.080 --> 33:53.650
you come down here
and get it yourself.

33:53.760 --> 33:54.921
Yeah, he's not wrong, man.

33:55.040 --> 33:56.804
Right, if you're gonna take something,
at least--

33:56.880 --> 33:58.041
at least take some Bordeaux.

33:58.160 --> 33:59.685
- [Dion] You getting that?
- [Starvos] Oh, yeah, yeah.

33:59.760 --> 34:01.728
Oh, and the, uh-- the Fattoria '07.

34:02.120 --> 34:04.441
<i>[Tommy]
No, no, no, that's-- that's the '09.</i>

34:04.840 --> 34:07.127
That's total junk.
Don't you know anything?

34:07.200 --> 34:09.521
No, we don't know anything, man.
You're the somm.

34:09.639 --> 34:11.768
<i>Okay, you know what? Go to the next aisle.</i>

34:13.080 --> 34:14.922
- There, right there. Right there.
- What, <i>this?</i>

34:15.040 --> 34:18.089
Gra-- grab the Châteauneuf.
Yes, that stuff's like a dream.

34:18.320 --> 34:20.971
<i>[Tommy]
Get two cases. Yeah, actually,</i>

34:21.440 --> 34:24.569
- yeah, get four.
- Happy? Huh? Grateful?

34:24.840 --> 34:27.081
You want to tickle my balls
right now, don't you?

34:27.159 --> 34:29.049
Love you, man.
[smooches]

34:29.120 --> 34:30.167
[engine starts]

34:32.360 --> 34:33.440
Pilar?

34:33.639 --> 34:34.641
Mose, start loading up.

34:34.760 --> 34:36.364
Wait, wait, did anybody get my grappa?

34:36.440 --> 34:38.726
- Oh, forget your grappa.
- I'm getting my damn grappa.

34:38.800 --> 34:40.245
Fine, we'll get your grappa.

34:43.360 --> 34:45.123
Hey! What are you doing here?

34:45.440 --> 34:48.728
[groans, gasps for air]

34:50.480 --> 34:53.210
Mose, man! What did you do?

34:54.440 --> 34:55.851
He surprised me.

35:02.880 --> 35:05.929
2003 red Bottini, retails at...

35:07.800 --> 35:09.165
About $350.

35:09.240 --> 35:13.962
And I offer it to you at the low,
low price of, hmm, free.

35:17.440 --> 35:18.965
Dude, what's wrong?

35:19.360 --> 35:22.682
We're here to celebrate, baby.
We're on our way. What's the matter?

35:22.760 --> 35:24.922
[groans] Don't get me wrong.
I'm happy about the wine.

35:25.000 --> 35:27.207
It's just, you know, Frank.

35:27.280 --> 35:29.169
Oh, Frank's insurance will cover the cost.

35:29.240 --> 35:30.890
You know, he probably doubled the claim.

35:30.960 --> 35:32.883
You know what?
We actually did him a favor.

35:32.960 --> 35:35.770
- [cellphone ringing]
- Maybe.

35:38.640 --> 35:39.971
Hello?

35:40.560 --> 35:42.210
Oh, hey, Blake. What...?

35:43.040 --> 35:44.166
No.

35:45.960 --> 35:46.961
What?

35:47.920 --> 35:49.001
Jesus, what-- ?

35:49.520 --> 35:52.205
Th-- that's terrible.

35:52.280 --> 35:54.362
No, um-- No. Thank you.

35:54.880 --> 35:55.927
Later.

35:57.800 --> 35:59.040
What?

35:59.800 --> 36:02.041
Did you happen to leave
anything out when you told me

36:02.160 --> 36:04.083
about your little wine adventure?

36:04.160 --> 36:05.241
No. What you talking about?

36:05.320 --> 36:08.642
- Any, I don't know, horrific details?
- No, what?

36:08.720 --> 36:10.802
- Wait, who was that?
- That was a wine-rep friend.

36:10.880 --> 36:15.204
Apparently, there was a big
robbery at Frank's warehouse,

36:15.280 --> 36:17.487
and, uh, somebody got hurt... bad.

36:18.400 --> 36:20.164
Randy, the security guy?

36:20.280 --> 36:22.442
Yeah, oh, that. Yeah, that...

36:22.520 --> 36:24.807
- Yeah, that was unfortunate.
- Unfortunate?

36:25.840 --> 36:28.571
Randy's got a collapsed trachea
and a shattered kneecap.

36:28.760 --> 36:30.364
That's called collateral damage.

36:30.440 --> 36:31.487
This is not okay.

36:31.680 --> 36:33.045
Trust me, he'll live, all right?

36:33.120 --> 36:35.248
The important thing
is that we got our wine.

36:35.880 --> 36:37.644
Damn it, Dion!

36:39.000 --> 36:40.047
We're not criminals!

36:40.240 --> 36:41.924
This is the kind of shit
my dad does!

36:42.040 --> 36:43.087
But he's successful!

36:44.680 --> 36:47.251
T., opening a restaurant in the Bronx

36:47.320 --> 36:49.004
is not exactly an easy proposition.

36:49.440 --> 36:50.566
You know, if we're gonna make it,

36:50.640 --> 36:52.688
you know, we may-- we may have
to get our hands dirty.

36:52.760 --> 36:54.842
I'm not talking about
getting our hands dirty.

36:54.920 --> 36:56.684
I'm talking about almost killing a guy.

36:56.960 --> 37:00.931
Oh, so it's okay to steal
$100,000 worth of wine.

37:01.000 --> 37:02.889
It's okay to take
your dad's dirty money,

37:02.960 --> 37:05.247
but, oh, if poor, schmucky Randy
gets his leg broken,

37:05.320 --> 37:07.402
then, what, suddenly,
you have a conscience? No.

37:07.480 --> 37:08.606
Yes!

37:09.760 --> 37:11.250
All right, fine.

37:11.440 --> 37:13.681
Let's talk to Randy.

37:15.800 --> 37:17.643
Oh, hello. Is that Randy?

37:18.120 --> 37:21.522
Oh, good. Good.
'Cause screw you, Randy!

37:22.240 --> 37:23.241
[scoffs]

37:24.360 --> 37:25.930
Yeah, go on. Say it.

37:26.120 --> 37:28.202
[chuckles] No.

37:28.280 --> 37:30.089
Yeah, if Randy is what stands between us

37:30.280 --> 37:33.489
and our restaurant, say it.

37:34.480 --> 37:36.130
- Stupid.
- [Dion] Oh, really?

37:36.640 --> 37:39.291
What, you, uh, you--
you don't want to do this restaurant?

37:39.400 --> 37:40.447
[scoffs]

37:41.240 --> 37:42.287
Say it.

37:46.640 --> 37:48.927
Screw you, Randy. Okay?

37:49.000 --> 37:51.207
No. Come here. Come here.

37:52.280 --> 37:53.441
Take a look at this.

37:53.920 --> 37:57.163
Huh? Look at all that wine, bro.

37:59.080 --> 38:00.127
[Dion] It's all ours.

38:01.000 --> 38:02.161
It's for the restaurant.

38:03.360 --> 38:06.807
Now... say it like you mean it.

38:12.200 --> 38:13.406
Screw you, Randy.

38:13.640 --> 38:16.564
Yeah, Randy was gonna crush Rie's dream.

38:17.920 --> 38:21.891
- <i>Screw</i> you, Randy.
- All our sketches, all our hard work,

38:21.960 --> 38:23.450
you having to crawl back
to your dad--

38:23.520 --> 38:24.646
All of that would have been for nothing.

38:24.720 --> 38:26.882
Screw you, Randy,

38:26.960 --> 38:30.567
you stupid son of a bi--
You waste of space!

38:30.640 --> 38:31.687
Why don't you just 90"

38:31.760 --> 38:32.841
Okay, okay, we-- we got it.

38:32.920 --> 38:35.048
We got it. Good.

38:37.720 --> 38:39.210
Hey, T., look at me.

38:40.760 --> 38:43.161
Nothing's gonna stop us. Hmm?

38:43.680 --> 38:45.125
Nothing.

38:49.600 --> 38:53.002
[guitar music plays]

38:53.600 --> 38:55.921
[school bell rings,
indistinct conversations]

38:58.600 --> 39:00.409
Have one of your parents call me, okay?

39:01.440 --> 39:04.523
[boy] It'll have to be my dad.
My mom's in jail.

39:05.920 --> 39:07.604
Okay.

39:19.600 --> 39:22.444
- Hey, yo, what the hell?
- A Mexican gal let me in.

39:23.840 --> 39:28.368
So, word on the street
is someone stole the Asian coke shipment.

39:28.600 --> 39:30.967
What, the coke shipment that--
that I told you about.

39:31.040 --> 39:32.690
Our mutual friend's got it, right?

39:32.920 --> 39:33.967
Couldn't say.

39:34.680 --> 39:36.091
I'm thinking he does,

39:36.160 --> 39:38.686
and he's too smart to put it
on the street right now.

39:39.360 --> 39:41.089
But nobody keeps cocaine
as a hobby,

39:41.280 --> 39:43.248
and when he sells it,
there's gonna be a lot of cash.

39:43.400 --> 39:45.721
I need to find out where
he's laundering his money.

39:47.400 --> 39:48.845
What do you expect me
to do about it?

39:48.920 --> 39:52.049
Get in closer with him.
Keep your ear to the ground.

39:53.640 --> 39:56.007
[mid-tempo music plays]

39:57.200 --> 39:59.407
I swear to God, I am this close.

40:07.640 --> 40:10.928
<i>I have three businesses ready
to sign leases on the new lot.</i>

40:11.080 --> 40:12.411
<i>Glad to hear it.</i>

40:12.800 --> 40:14.211
[Woichik Jr.] And I'm happy to report

40:14.280 --> 40:16.328
<i>I received a very nice payment
from Dion Patras.</i>

40:16.400 --> 40:21.725
And the Chinese food
is divided and well-hidden.

40:21.960 --> 40:23.041
[Woichik Sr.] Good.

40:23.120 --> 40:25.885
<i>As for the territory of the South Bronx...</i>

40:27.560 --> 40:28.607
[screaming]

40:29.960 --> 40:31.485
[muffled shouting]

40:35.680 --> 40:36.727
[speaks Polish]

40:37.720 --> 40:38.926
[muffled shouting]

40:46.440 --> 40:47.965
[horns honking in the distance]

40:49.160 --> 40:51.640
[guitar music plays]

40:59.040 --> 41:00.644
Hey, Dion, come here.

41:00.800 --> 41:02.131
Come here. Look at this.

41:02.480 --> 41:03.527
Look.

41:05.040 --> 41:06.644
We're bringing it to life.

41:09.240 --> 41:12.722
And these wines, my God.
Okay, um, here. Here.

41:13.240 --> 41:14.401
Taste this.

41:15.280 --> 41:17.487
Right? And now this.

41:23.400 --> 41:26.210
- Oh, my God. My God.
- [laughs]

41:26.280 --> 41:28.521
- Where'd the tart come from?
- Preserved lemon.

41:28.600 --> 41:30.170
- Val added it to the braised rabbit.
- Mmm!

41:30.240 --> 41:32.163
Meshes right in with that Riesling.

41:32.320 --> 41:34.368
- Insane, right?
- Oh, no, really, that-- that--

41:34.480 --> 41:35.481
that is close to perfect.

41:35.560 --> 41:37.881
Tommy? Your dad's here.

41:40.240 --> 41:41.480
Why are you here?

41:42.240 --> 41:43.969
To introduce Kevin,

41:45.120 --> 41:46.531
your Chef.

41:47.040 --> 41:48.530
Dion's the chef.

41:48.880 --> 41:51.690
You don't get to just show up
and say who does what.

41:51.760 --> 41:53.410
The contract you signed says I can.

41:53.680 --> 41:55.523
Wait-- wait, is that true?

41:55.600 --> 41:57.841
I told you there were
issues with the contract,

41:57.920 --> 41:59.809
and you said they'd go away.

42:04.120 --> 42:05.451
Dion Patras, right?

42:06.520 --> 42:08.443
It's an honor to have you working for me.

42:09.760 --> 42:10.921
Let's get started.

